item.title: Anki Guide for Medical Students
item.dc:creator: Durga Kullakanda
item.description: This guide is intended for medical students who are wanting to learn about what Anki is and how to use it in medical school. The Anki software is intimidating when first starting to use it, so this guide will teach the basics of navigating the program, making flashcards to study, and how to get the most benefit from studying those flashcards. Later sections will also get into the finer details of the program, which will be useful to know as you get familiar with Anki and would like to tweak things to best fit your needs.
